# make pdays into binned categories
bankdata$pdays <- case_when(bankdata$pdays == 999 ~ "not contacted", 
                          bankdata$pdays %in% c(0:5) ~ "recently",
                          bankdata$pdays %in% c(6:21) ~ "not recently")
bankdata$pdays <- as.factor(bankdata$pdays)


removeloanunknown <- which(bankdata$loan == "unknown")
bankdata <- bankdata[-removeloanunknown,]

#Check for multicollinerity 
correlation <- select_if(bankdata, is.numeric) 
correlation_matrix = cor(correlation)
corr_high = findCorrelation(correlation_matrix, .75, names = T)

# Partition, test and train -----------------------------------------------
set.seed(0)

#split clean data into train and test
#This will create an 80/20 split of randomly selected row numbers with 80% train 20% test
bank.Index<-createDataPartition(y=bankdata$y, 
                                p = .8,list = FALSE,times = 1)

# assign the test and train rows to their own data sets
bankTrain<-bankdata[bank.Index,]
bankTest<-bankdata[-bank.Index,]

#Sanity check to verify data has been split 80/20
dim(bankdata)

# Model Selection ----------------------------------------------------------------


# create null and full models
model.null = glm(y ~ 1, 
                 data = bankTrain,
                 family = binomial) # null model : no predictor
model.full = m1

# stepwise selection with BIC
step.models.BIC<-step(model.null, scope = list(upper=model.full),
                      direction="both",test="Chisq", trace = F, k=log(nrow(bankTrain)))

# stepwise selection with AIC
step.models.AIC<-step(model.null, scope = list(upper=model.full),
                      direction="both",test="Chisq", trace = F)

                   bankTest$y) #Predicted Probability and True Classification

false.rates <-performance(pred, "fpr","fnr")
accuracy <-performance(pred, "acc","err")

perf <- performance(pred, "tpr","fpr")
plot(perf,colorize = T, main = "ROC Curve")
text(0.5,0.5, paste("AUC:", auc))

plot(unlist(performance(pred, "sens")@x.values), unlist(performance(pred, "sens")@y.values), 
     type="l", lwd=2, 
     ylab="Sensitivity", xlab="Cutoff", main = paste("Maximized Cutoff\n","AUC: ",auc))

     type="l", lwd=2, col='red', ylab="", xlab="")

               contact + month + day_of_week + campaign + pdays + previous +
